M-1600-HU-07BF	Unknown (He was a Jesuit)	Unknown (It's mentioned as V. Reverencia')'	Spanish	The letter is from a Jesuit from the school in Arequipa who gives a day-by-day account of the Eruption of the Omate volcano (Huaynaputina): from Friday 18 February to Saturday 26 February. For each of the days, the author refers to the ash rain, the thunderstorm with lightning and thunder, the Earthquakes and the darkness both day and night experienced by the inhabitants of Arequipa. He also dwells on the processions and sermons given by the Society of Jesus, the Augustinians and the Dominicans, and on the behaviour and emotions of the population (confessions, penitence, terror, sadness, etc.). Only at the end of the letter, which must have been written on different days, does the author mention that news has arrived that it might be about a volcano near the town of Omate. The anonymous Jesuit also focuses on the material damage caused by the Eruption and its effects on other localities more or less distant from Arequipa.	https://archive.org/details/Mhsi120	Rome, Archivum Romanum Societatis Jesu, Peru 19, ff. 70 et seq.	1600		clihvzlwl000co3wswn9a9q52	\N	clilwaoiq0047o3nu8ro041pe
